.TH DOTCTL 1 "April 2026" "dotctl 1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
dotctl \- unified theme controller for cava, kitty, mako, wofi, waybar, tty-clock, hyprland, hyprpaper
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B dotctl
.I command
.RI [ args ...]
.br
.B dotctl
.I command
.BR \-h | \-\-help
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B dotctl
is a shell CLI that changes the color, font, font size, and other presentation
axes of five user-interface elements (plus an optional sixth,
.BR tty-clock ),
one hyprland color/effect axis, and one wallpaper axis in a single command
against a coordinated state file. It reads themed source configurations from
standard locations under
.IR ~/.config/ ,
copies or palette-injects the selected variant into the live config slot each
app reads, and signals the running daemon where applicable.
.PP
The controlled axes are:
.TP
.B cava
Color-only axis. Active file:
.IR ~/.config/cava/config .
.TP
.B kitty
Color, font, font size. Active file:
.IR ~/.config/kitty/kitty.conf .
Font size is applied by
.BR sed (1)
against the active copy only; themed sources stay canonical.
.TP
.B mako
Color, font, font size. Active file:
.IR ~/.config/mako/config .
Reloaded via
.BR makoctl (1).
.TP
.B wofi
Color, font, font size, subvariant
.RB ( 1
or
.BR 2 ).
Active file:
.IR ~/.config/wofi/style.css .
.TP
.B waybar
Color, font, font size, style
.RB ( pill
or
.BR console ),
scope
.RB ( full
or
.BR minimal ),
decorator glyph set
.RB ( pointed
or
.BR round ,
console-only),
VPN module toggle, transparent-bar toggle, explicit bar opacity (used when
transparent is off), and launcher logo (the distro glyph in the
.B custom/launcher
module). Active files:
.IR ~/.config/waybar/config.jsonc
and
.IR ~/.config/waybar/style.css .
Font size is rewritten by
.BR sed (1)
inside the
.B #waybar
block, the palette is injected into the
.B @define-color
block on every apply, the launcher glyph is rewritten inside the
.B custom/launcher
block, and the VPN module is stripped from both files when disabled. Reloaded
with
.BR "pkill -SIGUSR2 waybar" .
.TP
.B tty-clock
.IR (optional) .
Color-only axis. tty-clock has no native config format, so dotctl copies a
shell-sourceable fragment (defining
.BR TTYCLOCK_ARGS )
from
.IR ~/.config/tty-clock/<color>/config
to the active
.IR ~/.config/tty-clock/config .
Users run
.B tty-clock-themed
(a thin wrapper shipped as a dotctl module) which sources the active file and
execs
.BR tty-clock (1)
with the themed color plus any user-supplied flags. If the user declined
tty-clock at install time, the entire axis is skipped silently everywhere
(apply, show, list, configure, set, sync).
.TP
.B hypr
Color + window effect
.RB ( shadow
or
.BR glow ).
Writes
.I ~/.config/hypr/dotctl-colors.conf
from the hypr color template and the active waybar palette. Hot-reloaded via
.BR "hyprctl reload" .
Sourced by the user's
.I hyprland.conf
via a one-line
.B source =
directive.
.TP
.B wallpaper
An independent axis whose themes are directories under
.IR ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/
each paired with a
.B cycle-hyprpaper-<name>
script in
.IR ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/ .
.PP
A separate cycle script per wallpaper theme lets
.B dotctl
drop in new wallpaper collections without code changes.
.B "dotctl scan"
can auto-generate those scripts from existing directories.
.SH COMMANDS
Every command below accepts
.B \-h
or
.B \-\-help
for detailed usage.
.TP
.BI "configure [--preset " name ]
Interactive wizard that walks every element in turn, offering numbered choices
for each axis with the current value marked. With
.B --preset
the wizard uses the preset's values as defaults instead of the current state.
Running
.B configure
is required before any other command on first use.
.TP
.B show
Pretty-print current state, show drift if any element has a color or font that
differs from the others, flag whether the active wallpaper has a matching UI
color theme, and surface warnings about orphan wallpaper dirs or cycle scripts
missing their counterpart.
.TP
.BI "set [" flags ...]
Change one or more axes. With no flags, prints current state (equivalent to
.BR "dotctl show" ).
See
.B OPTIONS
below for the full flag list.
.TP
.B apply
Re-read
.I ~/.config/dotctl/config
and re-apply every element. Use after hand-editing the state file, or as a
catch-up if a live config drifted. Does not write state.
.TP
.B watch
Watch
.I ~/.config/dotctl/config
and auto-apply on save. Uses
.BR inotifywait (1)
when available; falls back to 1-second mtime polling otherwise. Ctrl-C to
stop.
.TP
.BI "cycle " "target direction"
Step a cycle. The two entry points intended for keybinds.
.RS
.TP
.B "cycle wallpaper next|prev"
Delegates to
.IB ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/cycle-hyprpaper- $WALLPAPER
with verb
.B forward
or
.BR backward .
.TP
.B "cycle waybar next|prev"
Rotates through 4 waybar variants within the current
.BR WAYBAR_COLOR , " WAYBAR_FONT" ,
and every other waybar axis:
.BR pill_full ,
.BR pill_minimal ,
.BR console_full ,
.BR console_minimal .
Wraps around at either end.
.RE
.TP
.BI "sync " "target source"
Copy color (and font where both elements have a font axis) from source to
target. Never copies style, scope, variant, decor, vpn, transparent, or
opacity.
.I target
may be any single element (
.BR cava ", " kitty ", " mako ", " wofi ", " waybar ", " tty-clock ", " wallpaper
) or the keyword
.BR all ;
.I source
must be a single element.
.B tty-clock
is only reachable as a sync target or source when it was installed.
.sp
Examples:
.RS
.IP
.B "dotctl sync wallpaper waybar"
.br
.B "dotctl sync all kitty"
.br
.B "dotctl sync waybar cava"
.br
.B "dotctl sync tty-clock kitty"
.RE
.TP
.BI "list " axis
List valid values for one axis. Axes:
.BR colors ,
.BR cava-colors ,
.BR kitty-colors ,
.BR mako-colors ,
.BR wofi-colors ,
.BR waybar-colors ,
.BR tty-clock-colors ,
.BR fonts ,
.BR kitty-fonts ,
.BR mako-fonts ,
.BR wofi-fonts ,
.BR waybar-fonts ,
.BR styles ,
.BR scopes ,
.BR waybar-decors ,
.BR waybar-vpns ,
.BR waybar-transparents ,
.BR waybar-opacities ,
.BR hypr-effects ,
.BR launcher-logos ,
.BR wofi-variants ,
.BR waybar-variants ,
.BR wallpapers ,
.BR presets .
.BR "dotctl list help"
prints this axis list.
.TP
.BI "preset " "sub [name]"
Named snapshots of the full state. Subcommands:
.RS
.TP
.BI "save " name
Snapshot current state to
.IB ~/.config/dotctl/presets/ name .conf \fR.
.TP
.BI "load " name
Apply a preset (same effect as
.B "dotctl set --preset"
.IR name ).
.TP
.B list
List saved presets.
.TP
.BI "show " name
Print a preset's contents.
.TP
.BI "delete " name
Remove a preset.
.RE
.TP
.BI "new wallpaper " name
Scaffold
.IB ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/ name /
and
.IB ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/cycle-hyprpaper- name
from the 4-verb template. Edit the new script's
.B IMAGES=()
array to set the cycle order (or drop images in and run
.B "dotctl scan"
to auto-populate), then
.BI "dotctl set -w " name \fR.
Name must match
.BR [a-z0-9_]+ .
.TP
.BR "scan [--dry-run] [--force] [--update] [--prefix " \fIpath\fR ]
Walk the wallpaper root and generate
.B cycle-hyprpaper-*
scripts for any directory that doesn't already have one. Image lists are
populated from disk contents in alphabetical order (case-insensitive glob for
.BR .jpg ,
.BR .jpeg ,
.BR .png ,
.BR .webp ,
.BR .gif ,
.BR .bmp ,
.BR .jxl ).
Directory names must match
.BR [a-z0-9_]+ ;
others are reported as
.B invalid
and skipped. Existing scripts are preserved unless
.B --force
or
.B --update
is passed. Without either flag, directories whose image count differs from
the cycle script are reported as stale.
.B --update
merges new images into existing cycle scripts (appended at the end in
alphabetical order) and prunes entries for deleted files, preserving the
hand-curated ordering of existing entries.
.B --force
regenerates the entire script from scratch, replacing the
.B IMAGES=()
array with an alphabetically sorted list of current disk contents.
.B --dry-run
previews without writing.
.B --prefix
scans a non-canonical directory and hardcodes that path into the generated
scripts so a wallpaper pack can be used in place without moving it. Default
prefix is
.IR ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/ .
.TP
.B help
Print a top-level usage summary. Use
.BI "dotctl " "command " "--help"
for per-command help.
.SH OPTIONS
.B dotctl set
accepts these flags. Shortcut flags fan out across the elements they affect;
per-element flags take precedence. Precedence order is preset < shortcut <
per-element.
.SS Shortcut flags
.TP
.BI "-c, --color " color
Set color for cava, kitty, mako, wofi, and waybar - and for tty-clock
when it was installed at
.BR install.sh
time. The fan-out validates every element before touching state, so a
color that's missing for any installed element is rejected.
.TP
.BI "-f, --font " font
Set font for kitty, mako, wofi, and waybar. Cava and tty-clock have no
font axis.
.TP
.BI "--font-size " N
Set font size for kitty, mako, wofi, and waybar. Accepts integer or decimal
in the range
.BR "[4, 72]" .
.SS Per-element flags
.TP
.BI "--cava-color " color
.TP
.BI "--kitty-color " color
.TP
.BI "--kitty-font " font
.TP
.BI "--kitty-font-size " N
.TP
.BI "--mako-color " color
.TP
.BI "--mako-font " font
.TP
.BI "--mako-font-size " N
.TP
.BI "--wofi-color " color
.TP
.BI "--wofi-font " font
.TP
.BI "--wofi-font-size " N
.TP
.BI "--wofi-variant " N
.B 1
or
.BR 2 .
.TP
.BI "--waybar-color " color
.TP
.BI "--waybar-font " font
.TP
.BI "--waybar-font-size " N
.TP
.BI "-s, --waybar-style " style
.B pill
or
.BR console .
.TP
.BI "--waybar-scope " scope
.B full
or
.BR minimal .
.TP
.BI "--waybar-decor " decor
Console decorator glyph set.
.B pointed
or
.BR round .
Swaps the chevron / separator glyphs in
.B console_*
variants; has no effect on
.B pill_*
variants.
.TP
.BI "--waybar-vpn " on|off
Toggle the waybar VPN module. When
.BR on ,
.B vpnctl
and
.B vpn-status-indicator
must be available on
.BR PATH .
When
.BR off ,
the VPN block is stripped from both
.I config.jsonc
and
.IR style.css
on apply.
.TP
.BI "--waybar-transparent " on|off
Waybar bar background.
.B on
uses a fully transparent bar;
.B off
uses an opaque palette fill at the opacity given by
.BR --waybar-opacity .
.TP
.BI "--waybar-opacity " N
Waybar bar opacity, a decimal in
.BR "[0.0, 1.0]" .
Only takes effect when
.B --waybar-transparent
is
.BR off .
Wizard ladder:
.BR 0.05 ,
.BR 0.10 ,
.BR 0.15 ,
.BR 0.20 ,
.BR 0.30 ,
.BR 0.40 ,
.BR 0.50 ,
.BR 0.60 ,
.BR 0.70 ,
.BR 0.80 ,
.BR 0.90 ,
.BR 1.00 .
.TP
.BI "--tty-clock-color, --ttyclock-color " color
tty-clock palette. Only available when tty-clock was installed via
.BR install.sh
(the installer copies
.IR tty-clock_config/
into
.IR ~/.config/tty-clock/
and symlinks the
.B tty-clock-themed
wrapper onto PATH). Errors out with a pointer back to
.B install.sh
when the axis isn't present.
.TP
.BI "--hypr-effect " effect
Hyprland window effect.
.B shadow
draws a dark drop-shadow;
.B glow
replaces it with a colored glow matching the active border start color. Writes
.IR ~/.config/hypr/dotctl-colors.conf .
.TP
.BI "--launcher-logo " logo
Distro glyph for the waybar
.B custom/launcher
module. One of
.BR tux ,
.BR arch ,
.BR gentoo ,
.BR debian ,
.BR void ,
.BR nixos ,
.BR fedora ,
.BR fedora_inverse ,
.BR endeavouros ,
.BR cachyos ,
.BR opensuse ,
.BR artix ,
.BR slackware ,
.BR slackware_inverse .
The glyph is rewritten into the active
.I config.jsonc
on every waybar apply, including cycles, so the choice sticks across
.B "dotctl cycle waybar"
rotations. Long alias:
.BR --waybar-launcher-logo .
.TP
.BI "-w, --wallpaper " theme
.TP
.BI "--preset " name
Load a preset as the baseline, then apply any other flags on top.
.SH HYPRLAND INTEGRATION
.B install.sh
drops two sourceable snippets into
.IR ~/.config/hypr/ :
.TP
.I dotctl-keybinds.conf
Ships the cycle and audio-output binds. Uses hardcoded
.B SUPER
.RB ( Mod4 )
and calls
.B dotctl
directly (no
.B ~/.local/bin
prefix) so placement in
.I hyprland.conf
does not matter.
.TP
.I dotctl-colors.conf
A neutral-grey stub on install; overwritten by
.B dotctl apply
with palette-driven values that include border colors and the active
shadow/glow effect.
.PP
Add these two lines to the
.B bottom
of
.I ~/.config/hypr/hyprland.conf
(later sources override earlier ones):
.PP
.EX
source = ~/.config/hypr/dotctl-keybinds.conf
source = ~/.config/hypr/dotctl-colors.conf
.EE
.PP
Then
.BR "hyprctl reload" .
The shipped binds are:
.PP
.EX
bind = SUPER ALT, Right, exec, dotctl cycle wallpaper next
bind = SUPER ALT, Left,  exec, dotctl cycle wallpaper prev
bind = SUPER ALT, Up,    exec, dotctl cycle waybar    next
bind = SUPER ALT, Down,  exec, dotctl cycle waybar    prev
bind = ALT SHIFT, A,     exec, audio-output aux
bind = ALT SHIFT, S,     exec, audio-output speaker
bind = ALT SHIFT, H,     exec, audio-output headset
bind = ALT SHIFT, L,     exec, audio-output bluetooth
bind = ALT SHIFT, M,     exec, audio-output toggle-mute
.EE
.PP
All other theme changes go through the CLI.
.B dotctl
never edits
.I hyprland.conf
itself.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotctl/config
24-field
.B KEY=value
state file, hand-editable, flock-guarded on writes. Regenerate with
.BR "dotctl configure" .
Older state files at
.I ~/.cache/dotctl/state
are automatically migrated to the new location on first run; older state
files without the
.BR *_FONT_SIZE ,
.BR WAYBAR_DECOR ,
.BR WAYBAR_VPN ,
.BR WAYBAR_TRANSPARENT ,
.BR WAYBAR_OPACITY ,
.BR WAYBAR_LAUNCHER_LOGO ,
.BR TTYCLOCK_COLOR ,
or
.B HYPR_EFFECT
fields are soft-migrated to defaults on load. The
.B TTYCLOCK_COLOR
field is allowed to be empty - users who declined tty-clock at install
time see it as a no-op everywhere.
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotctl/presets/<name>.conf
Saved presets.
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/cycle-hyprpaper-<theme>
Per-theme wallpaper cycle scripts, rendered from
.BR _cycle-hyprpaper.template .
Invoked by
.B "dotctl cycle wallpaper next|prev"
and regenerated on demand by
.BR "dotctl scan" .
.TP
.I ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/_cycle-hyprpaper.template
Template used by
.B "dotctl new wallpaper"
and
.BR "dotctl scan" .
.TP
.I ~/.cache/dotctl/lock
Lock file held during state writes and cycle operations.
.TP
.I ~/.cache/hyprpaper-cycle/index_<theme>
Per-wallpaper-theme current image index, maintained by cycle-hyprpaper-*
scripts.
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/dotctl/dotctl-colors.conf.tmpl
Hyprland color template used by
.BR "apply_hypr" .
.TP
.I /tmp/dotctl.log
Event log for
.B dotctl
(apply, cycle, sync, watch).
.TP
.I /tmp/cycle_hyprpaper.log
Event log for wallpaper cycle scripts.
.TP
.I ~/.config/<element>/<color>(_<font>)(/<variant>)/<file>
Themed source files, read-only from
.BR dotctl 's
perspective. Directory names are the canonical axes; a new color or variant is
available to
.B dotctl
simply by dropping the matching directory into place.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tty-clock/<color>/config
Per-color shell fragments sourced by the
.B tty-clock-themed
wrapper. Each defines a
.B TTYCLOCK_ARGS
array with the palette-matching
.B "-C <n>"
color code (and any default flags like
.BR -c
to center). Absent when the user declined tty-clock at install time.
.TP
.I ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/<theme>/
Wallpaper image directories, auto-discovered at runtime. A wallpaper theme is
considered installed when both this directory and a matching
.B cycle-hyprpaper-<theme>
script under
.I ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/
exist. Orphans in either direction are reported by
.BR "dotctl show" .
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
First-time setup:
.PP
.EX
dotctl configure
.EE
.PP
Unified theme switch:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set -c tokyo_night -f phoenix
.EE
.PP
Scale every font for a 4K display, then save as a preset:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --font-size 22
dotctl preset save tv
.EE
.PP
Keep the UI on forest but drift only waybar to gruvbox:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --waybar-color gruvbox
.EE
.PP
Switch waybar to console style, full scope, round decorators:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --waybar-style console --waybar-scope full --waybar-decor round
.EE
.PP
Opaque bar at 60% opacity:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --waybar-transparent off --waybar-opacity 0.60
.EE
.PP
Enable the VPN module (requires vpnctl + vpn-status-indicator on PATH):
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --waybar-vpn on
.EE
.PP
Swap hyprland to a colored glow instead of a drop shadow:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --hypr-effect glow
.EE
.PP
Change only the waybar launcher distro glyph (persists across cycles):
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --launcher-logo nixos
.EE
.PP
Set the tty-clock color (only when tty-clock was installed via install.sh):
.PP
.EX
dotctl set --tty-clock-color gruvbox
tty-clock-themed                      # launches with the themed palette
.EE
.PP
Re-unify after drift:
.PP
.EX
dotctl sync all kitty
.EE
.PP
Wallpaper-only change, UI untouched:
.PP
.EX
dotctl set -w gentoo
.EE
.PP
Load a display preset:
.PP
.EX
dotctl preset load laptop
.EE
.PP
Hand-edit the state file live:
.PP
.EX
dotctl watch &
$EDITOR ~/.config/dotctl/config
.EE
.PP
Add a new wallpaper theme by hand (curated cycle order):
.PP
.EX
dotctl new wallpaper forest
cp ~/Downloads/*.jpg ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/forest/
$EDITOR ~/.config/dotctl/cycle/cycle-hyprpaper-forest   # populate IMAGES=( )
dotctl set -w forest
.EE
.PP
Bulk-import several wallpaper themes (alphabetical cycle order):
.PP
.EX
mkdir ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/forest ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/retrowave
cp ~/Downloads/forest/*    ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/forest/
cp ~/Downloads/retrowave/* ~/Pictures/dotctl/wallpapers/retrowave/
dotctl scan                                   # generates both cycle scripts
dotctl set -w forest
.EE
.PP
Preview a scan without writing anything:
.PP
.EX
dotctl scan --dry-run
.EE
.PP
After adding new images to an existing wallpaper directory, update the
cycle script without losing curated ordering:
.PP
.EX
dotctl scan --update
.EE
.PP
Scan a wallpaper pack in place from a non-canonical location:
.PP
.EX
dotctl scan --prefix ~/Downloads/wallpaper-pack
.EE
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error: invalid arguments, missing source files, missing state, validation
failure, or subprocess failure.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Overrides the default
.I ~/.config
location.
.B dotctl
places its state directory (and every themed source dir it reads) under this
root.
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Overrides the default
.I ~/.cache
location.
.B dotctl
places its cache directory (lockfile) there.
.TP
.B EDITOR
Used in documentation examples for hand-editing cycle scripts and the state
file.
